node.text:
🎥 & 📝: @twisted
INGREDIENTS
Bun:
240 ml whole milk, lukewarm
2 tsp fast action, dry yeast
1 tbsp sugar
2 large egg, whisked
1 ½ tsp salt
500g bread flour
84g soft butter
1 egg
Sesame seeds
 
Chicken:
8 large chicken breasts
3 cups flour
1 tbsp garlic powder
1 tbsp  onion powder
2 tsp baking powder
1 tsp salt
1 tsp pepper
 
8 eggs, whisked
½ cup vodka
Shredded iceberg lettuce
Big mac sauce:
1 ½ cups mayonnaise
2 tbsp yellow mustard
¼ cup relish
2 tsp sugar
1 tsp white wine vinegar
1 tsp paprika
½ tsp garlic powder
½ tsp onion powder
 
Shredded Lettuce
Chopped white onions
Sliced pickles

INGREDIENTS:
Dough:
240g (2 cups) glutinous rice flour 
55g (1/4 cup) caster sugar 
180ml boiling water
2 tbsp cooking oil
*divide dough in 20 portions each about 25g

Filling：
150g roasted ground peanuts
50g (1/4 cup) caster sugar 
3 tbsp peanut butter
*divide filling in 20 portions

Some sesame seeds for coating

node.text:
📷: @foodyeating #FOODY
-
Ingredients:
2 lb Pork Belly
1 tsp Salt
1 tsp Garlic Salt
1 tsp Onion Powder
Dry Rub
0.5 tsp Italian Seasoning
1 tsp Black Pepper Powder
1 tsp Cumin Powder
1 tsp Smoked Paprika
1.5 tsp Five Spice Powder
2 tsp Brown Sugarㅤ ㅤ ㅤ ㅤ ㅤ
Marinade For Pork Belly Skin
1 tsp White Vinegar
1 tsp Salt
1 tsp Olive Oil
-
Steps:
Mix salt, garlic salt, Onion Powder, Italian Seasoning, Black Pepper Powder, Cumin Powder, Smoked Paprika, Five Spice Powder, and Brown Sugar together.
Carve the pork belly horizontally and vertically. The cuts should be about 0.5 inches into the meat.
Apply the Dry Rub evenly onto the pork belly. Remember, do not apply it on the pork belly skin
Make a simple box with foil to wrap up the seasoned pork belly. Make sure the skin side is facing up.
Apply a layer of White Vinegar and a little bit salt. White Vinegar can help take away extra water from the meat
Bake it in the oven at a low temperature 90°C-110°C/200°F-220°F for an hour to dry the skin. This way, the skin is crispy
After an hour, take it out, Apply a layer of cooking oil on the skin. Then turn up the temperature at 200°C/400°F for 30-35 mins
Take it out when the time is up and cut it into small pieces. Serve and enjoy!
✏️by  @tastelife_recipes
Follow @foodyeating if you❣️food!
Tag a Hungry Friend! 👇🏼
